Name: Masada
Description: Masada - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient fortress and palace complex overlooking the Dead Sea.

Name: Old City of Acre
Description: Old City of Acre - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Historic walled port city with Crusader and Ottoman remains.

Name: White City of Tel-Aviv
Description: White City of Tel-Aviv – the Modern Movement - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Collection of over 4,000 Bauhaus-style buildings.

Name: Biblical Tels
Description: Biblical Tels – Megiddo, Hazor, Beer Sheba - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Three ancient settlement mounds mentioned in the Bible.

Name: Incense Route
Description: Incense Route – Desert Cities in the Negev - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient trade route with Nabataean cities.

Name: Baháʼi Holy Places
Description: Baháʼi Holy Places in Haifa and the Western Galilee - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Shrines and gardens of the Baháʼi Faith.

Name: Caves of Maresha and Bet-Guvrin
Description: Caves of Maresha and Bet-Guvrin in the Judean Lowlands - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Underground cave complexes from the Hellenistic period.

Name: Necropolis of Bet She'arim
Description: Necropolis of Bet She'arim: A Landmark of Jewish Renewal - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient Jewish burial complex.
